name: No authorization to relieve a person of administrative duty to provide specimens, samples, or print impressions
text: [§844D-73]  No authorization to relieve a person of administrative duty to provide specimens, samples, or print impressions.  Notwithstanding any other provision of law, a judge is not authorized to relieve a person of the separate administrative duty to provide specimens, samples, or print impressions required by this chapter if a person was found not guilty by reason of insanity or pleads no contest to a qualifying offense as defined in section 844D-31 or is given a deferred acceptance of plea under chapter 853. [L 2005, c 112, pt of §1]
